title: hydrangea
body:
A genus of [[flower]]ing plants of the [i]Hydrangeaceae[/i] family, native to southern and eastern Asia. Most species are [[bush|shrubs]], but some are small trees. Commonly called [b]hortensia[/b].

Hydrangeas bear globular or umbrella-shaped clusters of flowers that come out any time from early spring to late autumn in a variety of colors influenced by the pH level of the soil. Commonly depicted in shades of blue, purple, and pink.

In Japan, it is commonly associated with the [[rain]]y season. Its Japanese name is "ajisai" (アジサイ or 紫陽花), which refers specifically to [i]Hydrangea macrophylla[/i], the bigleaf hydrangea.

[[Ragnarok Online]]'s most famous dungeon, added in 2005 in Episode 10.2. Compared to most other dungeons featuring various monsters, the Bio Labs had enemies with names who mirrored the player classes. All of these factors made the Bio Labs one of the most popular spots to grind for levels and the rare monster cards.

title: trigram
body:
Eight diagrams used in Taoist cosmology to represent the fundamental principles of reality, seen as a range of eight interrelated concepts. Each consists of three lines, each line either "broken" or "unbroken," representing yin or yang, respectively. Due to their tripartite structure, they are often referred to as "trigrams" in English.

Most popularly used on [[Yakumo Yukari]]'s [[tabard]] on her [[Imperishable Night]] outfit, as well as [[Yagokoro Eirin]]'s dress.

title: zuihou_kai_ni_(kancolle)
body:
[[Zuihou (kancolle)|]]'s Kai Ni forms.

She obtained her second remodels with the February 21, 2018 update with Kai Ni and Kai Ni- B forms.

Clothing-wise, she changed little, a lattice-patterned strap connected to both sleeves being the only real noticable change. Gear-wise, she gained a flight deck apron (complete with a "Dzuho" imprint, her real-life identification mark), her "mysterious" back gear has been rebuilt as less mysterious armoring with AA guns attached and her quiver as her flight deck. She now wields a full sized yumi. Similarly to Zuikaku's own second remodels, Kai2 is distinguished as keeping her camouflage color scheme (her muneate gained some landing guidance stripes in the process) and Kai Ni- B reverts to her original red-white color scheme.

Stats-wise, Kai Ni is a significant upgrade from kai, complete with medium range; while Kai Ni- B is a more expansive remodel that sacrifices plane slots and evasion for a larger upgrade (including the highest max AA amongst Light Carriers), ASW capabilities (weaker than Taiyou) and Long range. Both remodels are available at level 80.

title: ukulele_apology_video_(meme)
body:
An infamous "apology" video posted by YouTuber Colleen Ballinger (formerly known by her online persona [[Miranda Sings]]) in June 28th 2023 in which she addresses the then-recent controversy revolving around her allegedly "engaging with young fans in inappropriate ways":https://knowyourmeme.com/memes/events/colleen-ballinger-and-adam-mcintyre-controversy.

The video came weeks after YouTuber Adam McIntyre shared his experiences of Ballinger purportedly having age-inappropriate conversations with him and various other young children in a group chat. Ballinger's decision to deliver her apology in the form of a [[ukulele]] song drew the ire of many internet commentators that believed the format to be too lighthearted to address the serious allegations levied against her, as well as trivializing the matters, prompting widespread backlash in the following days.

title: rainbow_mika
body:
[b]"Rainbow" Mika Nanakawa[/b], or [b]"Rainbow" Mika[/b] ([b]レインボー・ミカ[/b]) or [b]R. Mika[/b] for short, is a video game character from the [[Street Fighter]] fighting game series. Her first appearance is in [[street_fighter_zero_(series)|Street Fighter Zero 3]], later re-appearing in [[Street Fighter V]].

Mika is a Japanese [[wrestling|professional wrestler]] trained by the big, domineering, shinai-sporting, golf cart-riding [[Harmageddon Yoko]]. One of her favorite attacks (outside of grappling) is a flying [[hip attack]]. She is usually seen with her tag-team partner [[Yamato Nadeshiko (Street Fighter)|]]. She is considered the forefront representative of "joshipuro" (Japanese women's pro wrestling) in fighting games. [[Zangief]], a fellow pro wrestler, is her hero.

Mika is most commonly seen wearing a white and sky blue [[wrestling outfit]] of some design, complete with a [[domino mask]] serving as a [[wrestling mask]] around her [[blue eyes]] and her [[long hair|long]], [[blonde hair]] done up as [[twintails]].

Mika's goal is to be "Star of the Ring." To try to accomplish this, Mika decided she would travel abroad and battle famous street fighters even before she made her official debut. During that time, she met Zangief, a wrestler she is a huge fan of. Zangief inspired her as a pro wrestler to train hard for the next time they meet.

title: hori-san_to_miyamura-kun
body:
Lit. [i]Hori-san and Miyamura-kun[/i]

A 4koma manga by [[hero_(dka)|HERO]], that was first published online in February 2007 and adapted into an OVA in 2011. The first bound volume was released in 2008 by Square Enix.

It was later adapted into [i]Horimiya[/i], a standard format manga by [[Hagiwara Daisuke]], serialized in Square Enix's [i]GFantasy[/i], which was later adapted into an anime by [[CloverWorks]] in Q1 2021.

[[Hori Kyouko]] is a flashy high school girl, who, despite her ostentatious appearance, excels in academics and has a family-loving character. [[Miyamura Izumi]] is a bland high school boy, who, despite not wanting to stand out in class, secretly wears piercings outside of school and has a large body tattoo. One day, Miyamura finds Hori's little brother injured and helps him back to Hori's house, where the relationship between Hori and Miyamura begins with Hori's discovery of Miyamura's secret.

title: the_fast_and_the_furious:_tokyo_drift
body:
The third film in [[Fast & Furious]] saga, released in 2006. The film follows [[Sean Boswell]], a hot-headed American high schooler who gets sent to live with his father in [[Tokyo (city)|]] after a street racing wreck, and discovers the local [[drifting]] scene.

Tokyo Drift is largely credited for creating an increased interest in drifting and Japanese cars in America, and the movie's theme song (performed by Japanese rap group Teriyaki Boyz) is often used in [[meme]]s and edits about drifting to this day. Notable cars featured in the film include [[Han Lue|Han]]'s [[Veilside]] [[mazda rx-7 fd|FD RX-7]], Sean's [[Mitsubishi Lancer Evolution]], and the "Mona Lisa" [[Nissan Silvia S15]]. The film is also notable for real life drift legend [[Tsuchiya Keiichi]]'s involvement, as he was the stunt coordinator and one of the stunt drivers.

This entry is known as [b]Wild Speed X3 Tokyo Drift[/b] in Japan.

title: chuseok
body:
Chuseok , also known as Hangawi (from archaic Korean for "the great middle (of autumn)"), is a major mid-autumn harvest festival and a three-day holiday in South Korea celebrated on the 15th day of the 8th month of the lunar calendar on the full moon. In North Korea, they only celebrate for the day of chuseok. Like many other harvest festivals around the world, it is held around the autumn equinox, i.e. at the very end of summer or in early autumn. It is the biggest traditional holiday in South Korea.

h4. See also

Unlike the previous forms in the [[Frieza Clan]] (which either suppress their power of their real form, or is their real form in their Fourth and usually Final Form), his Fifth Form was a power-up similar to the [[Super Saiyan]] forms. The body changes include a growth in height, gaining spike protrusions and additional gem-like parts, natural [[red eyes]] becoming fully colored and [[no pupils|pupil-less]], and the inclusion of a [[mouth mask]].

In [[Dragon Ball Heroes]], Cooler would take advantage of his brother's [[Golden Frieza|Golden]] transformation and combine it with his fifth form to become [[Golden Cooler]].

title: bird_of_paradise_flower
body:
[i][b]Strelitzia[/b][/i] (commonly known as bird of paradise or crane flower) is a genus of five flowering plants in the family [i]Strelitziaceae[/i] native to the southern Africa. Its common name, [i]bird of paradise[/i], refers to the resemblance of the open flower to the head of an actual [[bird of paradise (bird)|]].

Bird of paradise produces exotic looking flowers, usually in shades of red, orange or yellow ([i]Strelitzia reginae[/i], [i]S. juncea[/i]), although some species are white ([i]Strelitzia alba[/i], [i]S. caudata[/i], [i]S. nicolai[/i]). Each flower sprouts from a beak-like sheath (called a spathe) that grows at right angles to the stem, creating the appearance of the bird's beak. The flowers consist of red to yellow sepals and purplish-blue or white petals. The leaves are tall and thick, arranged in a fan-like pattern.

title: bring_me_the_horizon
body:
Bring Me the Horizon (often abbreviated as BMTH) are a British rock band formed in Sheffield in 2004. The band is best known for their metalcore songs and their influence on the subgenre, although the band started out as a deathcore band with the release of their debut EP "This Is What The Edge Of Your Seat Was Made For" and debut album "Count Your Blessings"; and delved into nu-metal with the release of their sixth album "[[Amo (bring me the horizon)|]]", and returned to their aggressive roots with their EP "Post Human: Nex Gen", surprise-released on 24th May 2024. The band has collaborated with numerous other acts such as Lights, Ed Sheeran, SLANDER, Spiritbox, AURORA, Underoath and so on, and had won many awards including [i]Kerrang![/i] Awards, BRIT Awards, Alternative Press and nominated for Grammy Awards on various categories.

In the end of 2023, the band announced one of their member Jordan Fish leaving the band. Fish first worked with the band to assist the existing members to complete the band's fourth album "Sempiternal", with his notable work being "Can You Feel My Heart":[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QJJYpsA5tv8] from the album been widely used in the [[gigachad_(meme)|]] [[meme]]. The song became the most well-known song of the band as the result of the meme.

title: daijinryuu

A sentient mechanical dragon god that appears as a neutral antagonist in [[Gosei Sentai Dairanger]].

His counterpart in [[Mighty Morphin Power Rangers]] is [b]Serpentera[/b], a giant personal Zord of [[Lord Zedd]], and is co-piloted by [[grifforzer|Goldar]].

It is the most massive Zord ever created; the skycraper-sized Red Dragon Thunderzord is roughly the size of its hand. It resembles an Eastern Dragon in form, and has enough power to annihilate a planet. It attacks by firing out bolts of energy, and its colossal size allows to crush nearly any foe, although Tor the Shuttlezord could withstand it, if only barely. Its massive power brought the Power Rangers to the brink of defeat every time that it was called, and it failed to destroy them only because of its one weakness: the colossal amount of fuel that it needed to be powered.

title: takahashi_shotei_(style)
body:
Takahashi Shotei (also known as Takahashi Hiroaki) was a Japanese ukiyo-e artist active in the late 19th and early 20th centuries.
He is best known for his woodblock prints, which often depicted serene landscapes, nature scenes, and traditional Japanese settings.
Shotei was associated with the shin-hanga movement, which sought to revive traditional Japanese woodblock printing techniques while incorporating Western artistic influences.
His works are celebrated for their delicate use of color and fine details.

title: star_wars:_revenge_of_the_sith
body:
[[Star Wars]]: Episode III – Revenge of the Sith is a 2005 American epic space opera film written and directed by [[George Lucas]]. It stars [[Ewan McGregor]], [[Natalie Portman]], [[Hayden Christensen]], Ian McDiarmid, [[Samuel L. Jackson]], [[Christopher Lee]], Anthony Daniels, Kenny Baker and Frank Oz. The sequel to [[Star Wars: The Phantom Menace]] (1999) and [[Star Wars: Attack of the Clones]] (2002), it is the sixth film in the Star Wars film series and the final installment in the Star Wars prequel trilogy.

Revenge of the Sith is set three years after the onset of the [[Star Wars:  the clone wars|Clone Wars]] as established in Attack of the Clones. The [[Jedi]] are spread across the galaxy in a full-scale war against the Separatists. The Jedi Council dispatches Jedi Master [[Obi-Wan Kenobi]] on a mission to defeat [[General Grievous]], the head of the Separatist army and Count Dooku's former apprentice, to put an end to the war. Meanwhile, after having visions of his wife [[Padme Amidala]] dying in childbirth, Jedi Knight [[Anakin Skywalker]] is tasked by the Council to spy on [[Palpatine]], the Supreme Chancellor of the Galactic Republic and, secretly, the Dark Lord of the Sith Darth Sidious. [spoilers]Sidious manipulates Anakin into turning to the dark side of the Force and becoming his apprentice, [[Darth Vader]], with wide-ranging consequences for the galaxy.[/spoilers]

title: victorious_(kancolle)
body:
[i][[Kantai Collection]][/i] character [[personification|personifying]] "HMS [i]Victorious[/i], pennant number R38":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HMS_Victorious_(R38)#Service_with_the_US_Navy], third of four Illustrious-class aircraft carriers of the British Royal Navy. Like all British shipgirls before her, she was fleshed out by [[konishi (koconatu)|Konishi]]. Her voice actress is Yamada Misuzu.

Like some British shipgirls depicted in the game, she is given characteristics such as: [[long_hair|Long]] [[blonde hair]], greenish [[blue eyes]], and a [[medium_breasts|somewhat well-endowed bustline]]. She wears a somehat stylized [[military uniform]] comprising of a greenish [[cropped jacket]] over a [[white shirt|white]] [[dress shirt]] decorated with a [[red flower|red]] [[red_rose|rose]], a [[corset]] attached to an overskirt worn over a [[white_skirt|white]] [[underskirt]], [[black pantyhose]], [[rudder footwear]], [[black gloves]], and a [[pelvic curtain]] resembling an aircraft carrier runway. She also wears a [[tiara]]-like [[hairband]] similar to [[Ark Royal (kancolle)|]]'s. Her [[machinery|rigging]] includes a [[quiver]] to the right of her hip and she wields a [[compound bow]] with a distinct [[flight deck]] motif in her left hand.

Victorious has [[official_alternate_hair_length|also been depicted with]] [[short hair]], mirroring her voice actress's own hairstyle.

Her jacket's hue being close to "robin egg blue" is one of her official links to her brief time as part of the US Navy under the codename "USS [i]Robin[/i]" in 1943. Her seasonal Christmas voice line references this period too, which was unremarkable compared to the rest of her service. Such voice line also references her relationship with [[Saratoga (kancolle)|]], the only active American flight carrier that year to which the historical Victorious provided support. This period of her life service tends to be more fleshed out on fanarts.

Originally a depiction of [[Madotsuki]] from [[Yume Nikki]] attempting to contain her vomit, drawn by [[Aosora (Mizore)]]

 The drawing has been often used as a reaction image on imageboards to express disgust towards someone's opinion or facts, in addition to its use as exploitable template. As popularity of the image grew, the nickname "Vomit-Chan" was used over Madotsuki, sometimes replacing the name. The original image inspired derivates, all as a reaction to portray extreme dismay or disgust.

title: chinese_bellflower
body:
[b][i]Platycodon[/i][/b], commonly called Chinese bellflower, is a genus of [[flower]]ing plant in the [[bellflower]] family ([i]Campanulaceae[/i]), native to East Asia. The only member of the genus is [i]Platycodon grandiflorus[/i].

Chinese bellflower produces five-petaled, star-shaped flowers that are blue, purple, pink, or white in color. A notable feature is the [[bud]], which swells like a balloon before opening into a star-shaped flower, earning the flower another common name - [b]balloon flower[/b] (which is also a tag, but for literal balloons). The roots of the plant are edible and used in cooking.

Not to be confused with [[balloon flower]], a flower made by tying up a balloon. Also not to be confused with [[flower balloon]], a flower-shaped balloon.

title: claw_ring
body:
A [[ring]] that resembles an animal [[claws|claw]]. Although it's called a [[ring]], it's usually longer than a normal ring and covers the finger up to the first or second knuckle. It may also include a bendable joint.

Also known as a finger claw ring or a finger armor ring.

In China zhijiatao (指甲套) were worn during the Ming and Qing dynasties by nobility, to protect their long nails, which were in fashion for men and women. Images depicting [[hanfu]] and machu wear from these eras often include what is called a "claw ring" on this site.

title: fedorov_avtomat
body:
The [b]Fedorov Avtomat[/b] (Автома́т Фёдорова) is a Russian select-fire [[rifle]] designed by [[Vladimir Grigoryevich Fyodorov]] in 1915. Originally chambered in 6.5×50mmSR Arisaka and fed from standard 25-round magazine, its fire rate ranges from 350 to 400 rounds per minute. Produced in the [[Russian Empire]] and later in the Soviet Union. The [[weapon]] saw limited use in World War I. 

It is considered to be an early predecessor of the modern [[battle rifle]] designs.

title: street
body:
A paved [[road]] in a [[city]] environment, usually designed for both vehicle and pedestrian traffic.

A street is a type of [[road]]. The difference between a road and a street is that [[road]] is for all types of roads, including [[highway]]s and [[dirt road]]s outside of cities, while a street generally refers to a paved road in a city. A street is usually designed to accommodate both vehicle and pedestrian traffic, with intersections, [[traffic light]]s, [[sidewalk]]s, and [[crosswalk]]s. A [[highway]] is usually designed only for high-speed or long distance vehicle traffic and doesn't have these features.

A street can be unpaved dirt, but is most often paved with a hard, durable surface such as asphalt, concrete, cobblestone or brick.

title: the_office
body:
[b]The Office[/b] is an American mockumentary sitcom TV series that depicts the everyday work lives of office employees at the Scranton, Pennsylvania, branch of the fictional Dunder Mifflin Paper Company. It aired on NBC from March 24, 2005, to May 16, 2013, spanning a total of nine seasons. 

Based on the 2001–2003 BBC series of the same name created by Ricky Gervais and Stephen Merchant, it was adapted for American television by Greg Daniels, a veteran writer for Saturday Night Live, [[King of the Hill]], and [[The Simpsons]]. It was co-produced by Daniels' Deedle-Dee Productions and Reveille Productions (later Shine America), in association with Universal Television. The original executive producers were Daniels, Gervais, Merchant, Howard Klein, and Ben Silverman, with numerous others being promoted in later seasons.

Like its British counterpart, the series was filmed in a single-camera setup without a studio audience or a laugh track to simulate the look of an actual documentary. The series debuted on NBC as a mid-season replacement and aired 201 episodes for its run. The Office originally featured [[Steve Carell]], Rainn Wilson, John Krasinski, Jenna Fischer, and B. J. Novak as the main cast; however, the series experienced numerous changes to its ensemble cast during its run. Notable stars outside the original main cast include Ed Helms, Amy Ryan, Mindy Kaling, Craig Robinson, James Spader, Ellie Kemper, and Catherine Tate.

The Office was met with mixed reviews during its short first season, but the following seasons, particularly Carell's performance, received significant acclaim from television critics as the show's characters, content, structure, and tone diverged considerably from the British version. These seasons were included on several critics' year-end top TV series lists, winning several awards such as a Peabody Award in 2006, two Screen Actors Guild Awards, a Golden Globe Award for Carell's performance, and four Primetime Emmy Awards, including one for Outstanding Comedy Series, in 2006. The eighth season was criticized for a decline in quality. Many saw Carell's departure in season seven as a contributing factor; however, the ninth and final season ended the series with a generally positive response. The series finale, which originally aired on May 16, 2013, was viewed by an estimated 5.7 million viewers and garnered critical acclaim. In 2016, Rolling Stone named The Office one of the 100 greatest television shows of all time.

title: itsuki_shu
body:
[i][[Ensemble Stars!]][/i] character. A third year student and member of [[valkyrie (ensemble stars!)|Valkyrie]]. 

He has [[short hair|short]] [[pink hair]] and [[purple eyes]]. At school, he wears the standard [[yumenosaki school uniform|Yumenosaki uniform]], consisting on [[plaid pants]], a [[blazer]] and a [[frilled neckwear|frilled]] [[necktie]]. For Valkyrie, he wears a [[top hat]], [[frilled jacket]] and a [[long coat]] with [[boots]].

He is an arrogant person who wants everything to go his way. Despite this, he does not like places with many people and is not very good at facing the crowds under lives. As the captain of the handicraft club, he has dexterous and skillful fingers, and made the uniforms of their unit by himself. He's also childhood friends with [[kiryu kuro|Kuro Kiryuu]]. Shu is a "shotacon" and sometimes fawns over cute little boys, like his former unit member [[nito nazuna|Nazuna Nito]] (Shu and Mika consider Nazuna a traitor for leaving Valkyrie, because the latter couldn't stand Shu anymore). [[kagehira mika|Mika Kagehira]] loves and respects him, but Shu is dismissive towards him.

He owns a [[doll]] named [[mademoiselle_(ensemble_stars!)|Mademoiselle]], which he uses to talk through with around people he's not confortable around.

At first he's hostile towards [[anzu (ensemble stars!)|Anzu]] because she and Trickstar got to defeat Fine and [[tenshouin eichi|Eichi Tenshouin]] by extension. He despises Eichi for the Five Oddballs incident, which caused Valkyrie (at the time the strongest unit) to fall from grace.

title: vladilena_millize
body:
Vladilena Milizé, nicknamed Lena, is a female main character from the light novel series [[86 -EightySix-]]. Lena is one of the Alba, a race characterized by their silver hair (appearing [[light blue hair|light blue]], [[white hair|white]], or [[grey hair|grey]]), and silver eyes (appearing [[grey eyes|grey]]). Lena has [[long hair]] with [[bangs]] that is usually unadorned and loose, with two [[antenna hair|antenna-like ahoge]].  

At the start of the series she is 16 years old, but through a combination of talent and connections has already obtained the commissioned officer rank of Major in the Republic of San Magnolia's military. Lena usually wears a San Magnolia military uniform, which is a blue [[military uniform]] composed of a [[blue jacket|blue]], [[high collar|high-collared]], [[long sleeves|long-sleeved]], [[cropped jacket]] with an [[armband]], a [[white shirt]] with blue and gold trim, a [[blue skirt|blue]] [[high-waist skirt]], a [[white belt|white]] [[o-ring belt|o-ring]] [[belt]] with one strap on one side and two straps on the other, a [[blue headwear|blue]] [[military hat|military]] [[peaked cap]], [[white thighhighs|white]] [[thighhighs]], and [[blue footwear|blue]] [[boots]].  She wears her uniform along with [[white thighhighs]] supported by [[garter straps]] (the author admitted this was due to his own fetish for [[garter belt]]s).

At the beginning of the series she is assigned as the handler of Spearhead Squadron and goes by the call sign Handler One.  After the events of the first cour of the anime/first volume of the light novel, Lena dyes a [[streaked hair|streak]] of her hair [[red hair|red]] and wears a black variant of her uniform, changing the color of her [[black jacket|jacket]], [[black skirt|skirt]], [[black headwear|hat]], [[black thighhighs|thighhighs]], and [[black footwear|boots]], thus including all five colors of the San Magnolia Republic's flag in her appearance.  She later obtains the nicknames "Bloody Reina" and "The Bloodstained Queen".

title: admiral_shinonome_harutora
body:
An admiral who takes his job seriously and can be a bit cranky when met with the much laid-back and playful [[Suzuya (kancolle)|]], who frequently bugs him for attention.

Has a muscular build and a short [[black hair]] left unkempt. He wears his [[military uniform|admiral uniform]] in a slovenly and informal manner and doesn't wear them in summer heat.

Likes [[Kamen Rider]] series, particularly [[Kamen Rider Drive]] and [[kamen rider black|Black]].

See post #2087860.

title: yamamoto_akira
